                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2003-11-09</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I agree with many that say that the first 150 pages are really worth reading.  They are beautiful and brilliant with images and gives you an inside seat as to how On the Road came about. Yet after that it is a tough read. The transcripts are long, go on forever and you wonder why they were included.  The last half of the book is pretty good. <p>This is defiantly one of those books you will want  to read when you have  the time, skill to concentrate , and desire for a wild ride. It took the two years to read this book and I am not a slow reader. But I was glad I had read it.</span>
                  
